  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p>Thursday 15th September 2016, Godalming, Surrey- There are few destinations that can boasts as spectacular landscape as <strong>Northern Norway</strong> from its <strong>breathtaking fjord coastline</strong> and <strong>mountainous landscapes</strong> to its <strong>snow-covered wilderness</strong> and m<strong>agnificent wildlife</strong>.</p>
<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/media/13052805/view_over_the_fjords.jpg" alt="Fjords Norway" width="486" height="325" rel="486,325" /></p>
<p>New for <a data-udi="umb://document/bd15fc7a3b704cf7aa7fee80236e0a9d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bd15fc7a3b704cf7aa7fee80236e0a9d}" title="Winter Wonderland">winter 16/17</a>, Inghams has expanding its <a data-udi="umb://document/336a323374f046cfa0591948e538170e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/336a323374f046cfa0591948e538170e}" title="Northern Fjord Norway">Norway</a> programme to include the three or four night Vesterålen Wildlife Adventure, which gives guests the chance to discover the area’s <strong>spectacular Arctic wildlife</strong> with a <strong>once-in-a-lifetime whale watching</strong> trip in the beautiful <strong>archipelago of Vesteralan</strong>, known as the Kingdom of the Whales. Visitors set off from the small town of Åndenes, on a three hour expedition led by a knowledgeable boat crew who will use their detection equipment to give visitors the best chance of seeing these magnificent mammals. The most common sight is the <strong>sperm whale</strong> but there is also a chance to spot pilot whales, minke whales, humpback whales, dolphins and killer whales. Those wanting to get a closer look can choose to head out on a<strong> RIB boat</strong> for an extra supplement.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>As well as <strong>whale watching</strong> the Vesterålen Wildlife Adventure includes a journey along the spectacular National Tourist Route, one of Norway’s most beautiful coastal routes, a visit to Blokken and its ‘Akvakultur’ <strong>fish farm</strong> where guests can <strong>try delicious Norwegian salmon</strong> and enjoy a<strong> boat trip</strong> to the salmon pens, a night-time ‘<strong>In Search of the Northern Lights</strong>’ safari and a unique experience of watching a classical concert in a former fishing oil tank.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Inghams is offering 3 nights departing 19 February 2017 from £989 per person, including direct flights from Gatwick or Manchester to Evenes, 3 nights accommodation in a 3* superior hotel, meals, all daytime excursions, daily buffet lunch on all excursions and return transfers. For more information visit <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk">www.inghams.co.uk</a> or contact 01483 79 11 01.</p>
